(("The University of New Mexico" "Main site feed" "https://news.unm.edu" (26704 42516 248839 484000) feed 0 nil nil ((title nil "The University of New Mexico") (link nil "https://news.unm.edu") (description nil "Main site feed") (language nil "en-us") (pubDate nil "Mon, 16 Jun 2025 21:04:08 GMT") (lastBuildDate nil "Mon, 16 Jun 2025 21:04:08 GMT") (generator nil "iPressroom") (item nil (title nil "Former law professor receives award for contributions to N.M. judicial education") (link nil "https://news.unm.edu/news/former-law-professor-receives-award-for-contributions-to-n-m-judicial-education") (content ((url . "https://s3.amazonaws.com/cms.ipressroom.com/175/files/20255/68504a9e3d633238e2d5b375_COVER/COVER_thmb.png") (fileSize . "2239726") (type . "image/png"))) (contentType nil "releases") (subtitle nil) (content nil "<![CDATA[<div class=\"textImage textImage-right\" style=\"float: right; width: 200px; margin: 10px 10px 10px; font-size: 90%; font-style: italic;\"><img align=\"right\" alt=\"bergman 1\" author=\"\" class=\"widget-image\" custom_size=\"true\" data-imgheight=\"278\" data-imgwidth=\"200\" file_id=\"68504ae93d633232a6d5b36d\" height=\"278\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/cms.ipressroom.com/175/files/20255/bergman+1.jpg\" title=\"\" width=\"200\" /></div>

<p>Former longtime University of New Mexico&nbsp;<a href=\"https://lawschool.unm.edu/\" rel=\"\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"\">School of Law</a> Professor Barbara Bergman received an award honoring her contributions to judicial education in New Mexico.</p>

<p>According to the Administrative Office of the Courts, Bergman was presented the <em>inaugural Rozier E. Sanchez CEI Faculty Award for excellence</em> from <a href=\"https://courteducation.nmcourts.gov/\" rel=\"\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"\">The New Mexico Court Education Institute </a>(CEI) during a ceremony at the annual training conference for state court judges in Albuquerque.</p>

<p>CEI Director Paula Couselo-Findikoğlu said Bergman embodies a &ldquo;passion for service, excellence in education and dedication to the rule of law.&quot;</p>

<p><!--StartFragment--><span data-olk-copy-source=\"MessageBody\">&quot;I am deeply touched to receive this award in honor of Judge Rozier Sanchez, who was dedicated to promoting judicial education. It is a humbling experience,&quot; she said. &quot;I am most grateful to New Mexico&rsquo;s amazing judiciary. I always enjoy coming to the Judicial Conclave. In preparation for that, I get to learn so much about the wonderful work the New Mexico courts do.&quot;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Bergman began her tenure at the UNM School of Law&nbsp;in 1987. Over the course of 28 years as a Lobo, she held numerous positions, including professor and associate dean for Academic Affairs in the school. Her primary focus was on criminal law, and she annually guided students through an intensive Evidence and Trial Practice course. </span></p>

<p><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">As a past president of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.nacdl.org/\" target=\"_blank\">National Association of Criminal Defense Lawyers</a>, Bergman received the highest honor awarded by the organization in 2001, among various other accolades. She has also taught at the annual New Mexico Judicial Conclave for three decades.</span></p>

<p>After leaving UNM&nbsp;in 2016, she became the director of Advocacy at the James E. Rogers College of Law, University of Arizona.</p>

<p><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><em><strong>Top photo credit: Administrative Office of the Courts</strong></em></span></p>
