<p>CTL recently awarded the prestigious Golden Paw Award to a select group of instructors. The Golden Paw Award is the highest recognition for online instruction at UNM.</p>

<div class=\"textImage textImage-right\" style=\"float: right; width: 200px; margin: 10px 10px 10px; font-size: 90%; font-style: italic;\"><img align=\"right\" alt=\"goldenpawseal\" author=\"\" class=\"widget-image\" custom_size=\"true\" data-imgheight=\"200\" data-imgwidth=\"200\" file_id=\"68489c163d63321f4bd5b358\" height=\"200\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/cms.ipressroom.com/175/files/20255/goldenpawseal.png\" title=\"\" width=\"200\" /></div>

<p>Additionally, UNM Online has introduced the Foundational Course Design Review, an initiative available to all online instructors at&nbsp;UNM&#39;s main campus. Through a Foundational Course Design Review, instructors receive feedback from an external review to improve their online courses.</p>

