]]>") (categories nil (category nil "Lobo Hub") (category nil "Institutional Support Service") (category nil "KNME")) (modDate nil "Fri, 13 Jun 2025 11:23:30 GMT") (relatedPages nil) (description nil "This week on New Mexico in Focus, questions remain for Santa Fe's Institute of the American Indian Arts (IAIA) as the school's federal funding is threatened to be cut. Robert Martin, president of the institute, gave Senior Producer Lou Divizio his...") (enclosure ((url . "https://s3.amazonaws.com/cms.ipressroom.com/175/files/20237/NMiF+Logo.jpg") (length . "60975") (type . "image/jpeg"))) (guid ((isPermaLink . "true")) "https://news.unm.edu/news/nmif-looks-at-juneteenth-and-pride-in-n-m-iaia-funds-threatened") (pubDate nil "Fri, 13 Jun 2025 11:19:00 GMT"))) ("Making trees in fire-maintained forest less susceptible to drought" "Recently published research from a Ph.D. graduate from the biology department at The University of New Mexico finds that frequent fires have the potential to reduce tree water stress." "https://news.unm.edu/news/making-trees-in-fire-maintained-forest-less-susceptible-to-drought" (26699 9136) new 9 nil nil ((title nil "Making trees in fire-maintained forest less susceptible to drought ") (link nil "https://news.unm.edu/news/making-trees-in-fire-maintained-forest-less-susceptible-to-drought") (content ((url . "https://s3.amazonaws.com/cms.ipressroom.com/175/files/20255/684343533d6332577e48c7e8_IMG_5484+copy/IMG_5484+copy_thmb.png") (fileSize . "18060196") (type . "image/png"))) (contentType nil "releases") (subtitle nil) (content nil "<![CDATA[<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW69496005 BCX0\">
<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW69496005 BCX0\" paraeid=\"{fc923324-6491-4cd1-a3e6-304e0cb5b7c2}{27}\" paraid=\"153016814\"><span class=\"TextRun SCXW69496005 BCX0\" data-contrast=\"auto\" lang=\"EN-US\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW69496005 BCX0\"></span></span></p>

<p>Recently <a href=\"https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/gcb.70284\" rel=\"\" target=\"\" title=\"\">published research</a> from a Ph.D. graduate from the biology department at The University of New Mexico finds that frequent fires have the potential to reduce tree water stress. Kevin Willson, a postdoctoral researcher with the Forest Service, found that fire-maintained forests had fewer trees with increasingly less water stress than fire-excluded forests.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<div class=\"textImage textImage-left\" style=\"float: left; width: 360px; margin: 10px 10px 10px; font-size: 90%; font-style: italic;\"><img align=\"left\" alt=\"IMG_5468 copy\" author=\"\" class=\"widget-image\" custom_size=\"false\" data-imgheight=\"270\" data-imgwidth=\"360\" file_id=\"684343ad3d6332577e48c817\" height=\"270\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/cms.ipressroom.com/175/files/20255/684343ad3d6332577e48c817_IMG_5468+copy/IMG_5468+copy_mid.png\" title=\"\" width=\"360\" /></div>

<p>&quot;Restoring frequent fire to these forests reduces forest density and competition for water, increasing the amount of water available per tree, which can improve tree response to drought,&quot; said Willson.&nbsp;&quot;As forests have become more flammable and prone to drought effects, determining how frequent fires affect tree response to drought is necessary to forecast how forests will function in response to future disturbances.&quot;&nbsp;</p>

<p>To assess tree response to drought following frequent-fire, Willson and his team compared tree growth and water stress before, during, and after two multi-year droughts (1996-2018) in fire maintained forests of the Gila Wilderness, where fires have been allowed to burn since 1975, and nearby areas that have not experienced a fire since at least 1909.&nbsp;</p>

<p>They found that frequent fires do not inhibit tree growth during drought but reduce&nbsp;forest density, which increases water availability for the remaining trees. Therefore, the reintroduction of frequent, low-severity fire regimes has the potential to moderate some effects of droughts on forests as climate change intensifies.&nbsp;</p>

<p>&ldquo;This work demonstrates that there is value beyond just hazardous fuels reduction from restoring frequent fire in ponderosa pine forests. It demonstrates that regular fire can increase tree resilience to drought,&rdquo; said UNM biology professor Matthew Hurteau.</p>

<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW69496005 BCX0\" paraeid=\"{fc923324-6491-4cd1-a3e6-304e0cb5b7c2}{27}\" paraid=\"153016814\"><span class=\"TextRun SCXW69496005 BCX0\" data-contrast=\"auto\" lang=\"EN-US\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW69496005 BCX0\"></span></span></p>
</div>

<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW69496005 BCX0\">
<p class=\"Paragraph SCXW69496005 BCX0\" paraeid=\"{fc923324-6491-4cd1-a3e6-304e0cb5b7c2}{194}\" paraid=\"779397350\"><span class=\"EOP SCXW69496005 BCX0\" data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;134233117&quot;:false,&quot;134233118&quot;:false,&quot;335559738&quot;:0,&quot;335559739&quot;:0}\"></span></p>
</div>
]]>") (categories nil (category nil "Inside UNM") (category nil "College of Arts & Sciences") (category nil "Biology") (category nil "Latest News") (category nil "Graduate Studies")) (modDate nil "Thu, 12 Jun 2025 20:25:54 GMT") (relatedPages nil) (description nil "Recently published research from a Ph.D. graduate from the biology department at The University of New Mexico finds that frequent fires have the potential to reduce tree water stress. ") (enclosure ((url . "https://s3.amazonaws.com/cms.ipressroom.com/175/files/20255/IMG_5468+copy.png") (length . "21270762") (type . "image/png"))) (author nil "Anna Padilla") (guid ((isPermaLink . "true")) "https://news.unm.edu/news/making-trees-in-fire-maintained-forest-less-susceptible-to-drought") (pubDate nil "Thu, 12 Jun 2025 19:00:00 GMT"))) ("UNM professor awarded prestigious Fulbright Distinguished Scholar honor" "Rosa Vallejos-Yopán, a linguistics professor at The University of New Mexico, has received the prestigious Fulbright Distinguished Scholar Award to further her research on Amazonian languages in Peru. " "https://news.unm.edu/news/unm-professor-awarded-prestigious-fulbright-distinguished-scholar-honor" (26698 56672) new 10 nil nil ((title nil "UNM professor awarded prestigious Fulbright Distinguished Scholar honor") (link nil "https://news.unm.edu/news/unm-professor-awarded-prestigious-fulbright-distinguished-scholar-honor") (content ((url . "https://s3.amazonaws.com/cms.ipressroom.com/175/files/20255/68432ac53d6332cec848c878_Rosa+traveling+along+the+Putumayo+River/Rosa+traveling+along+the+Putumayo+River_thmb.jpg") (fileSize . "978539") (type . "image/jpeg"))) (contentType nil "releases") (subtitle nil) (content nil "<![CDATA[<div class=\"textImage textImage-caption textImage-right\" style=\"float: right; width: 200px; margin: 10px 10px 10px; font-size: 90%; font-style: italic;\"><img align=\"right\" alt=\"Rosa Vallejos-Yopan\" author=\"\" class=\"widget-image\" custom_size=\"true\" data-imgheight=\"250\" data-imgwidth=\"200\" file_id=\"68432acb3d6332cf3d48cc03\" height=\"250\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/cms.ipressroom.com/175/files/20255/Rosa+Vallejos-Yopan.jpeg\" title=\"Rosa Vallejos-Yopán\" width=\"200\" />
<div class=\"textImage-captionBody\" style=\"padding: 3px 0px; clear: both;\">Rosa Vallejos-Yop&aacute;n</div>
</div>

<p><span>Rosa Vallejos-</span><span>Yop&aacute;n</span><span></span>, a linguistics professor at The University of New Mexico, has received the prestigious Fulbright Distinguished Scholar Award to further her research on Amazonian languages in Peru.&nbsp;This esteemed honor signifies Vallejos&#39; expertise in Amazonian languages and her research&rsquo;s impact on the communities she serves.&nbsp;</p>

<p>&ldquo;I was initially surprised to receive this award,&rdquo; said Vallejos. &ldquo;With the current federal funding cuts, I didn&rsquo;t think this would happen. I&rsquo;m incredibly grateful and excited to move my research forward.&rdquo;&nbsp;</p>

<p>Congress established the Fulbright Program in 1946 to promote awareness and foster friendly, peaceful partnerships with international communities and organizations; making collaboration a pillar of the program.&nbsp;</p>

<p><a href=\"https://fulbrightscholars.org/\">According to the Fulbright Scholar website</a>, the program awards over 400 grants in more than 135 countries to U.S. citizens for teaching, conducting research and working on professional projects worldwide.</p>

<p>Vallejos will partner with the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.ufsc.br/\">Federal University of Santa Catarina (UFSC)</a>&nbsp;in Florian&oacute;polis, Brazil. She will study how bilingual individuals pay attention to their surroundings and how that influences their daily language and grammar usage, focusing on bilingual speakers in Secoya villages in the Peruvian Amazon, where Spanish is on the rise.&nbsp;</p>

<div class=\"textImage textImage-caption textImage-left\" style=\"float: left; width: 200px; margin: 10px 10px 10px; font-size: 90%; font-style: italic;\"><img align=\"left\" alt=\"Rosa working with Secoya language consultant\" author=\"\" class=\"widget-image\" custom_size=\"true\" data-imgheight=\"250\" data-imgwidth=\"200\" file_id=\"68432ad13d6332cf2b48ca04\" height=\"250\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/cms.ipressroom.com/175/files/20255/Rosa+working+with+Secoya+language+consultant.jpeg\" title=\"Rosa working with a Secoya language consultant\" width=\"200\" />
<div class=\"textImage-captionBody\" style=\"padding: 3px 0px; clear: both;\">Rosa working with a Secoya language consultant</div>
</div>

<p>Her fieldwork will take place in a remote region of the Amazon. She will fly first to Iquitos, a city surrounded by rivers. From Iquitos, she will travel by a small airplane to the Peru-Colombia border, and from there by boat along the Putumayo river to reach the Secoya villages.&nbsp;</p>

<p>Vallejos&rsquo; colleague Naomi Shin, a professor within UNM&rsquo;s linguistics department and the Spanish and Portuguese department, explained, &ldquo;Dr. Vallejos-Yop&aacute;n&#39;s research demonstrates how linguistic structure reflects humans&#39; conceptualizations of the world around them. What we pay most attention to and how we view the world is what gets encoded in our languages,&rdquo; she said. &ldquo;This groundbreaking research has implications for all situations of language contact.&rdquo;&nbsp;</p>

<p>The award encompasses four months of research in Brazil. She will utilize a flexible travel model to conduct her research. Her first trip is scheduled for Oct.&nbsp;&nbsp;and Nov.&nbsp;&nbsp;of this year, followed by another two months in early spring 2026; March and April.&nbsp;</p>

<p>While in Florianopolis, she will collaborate with her colleagues at UFSC by teaching two mini-courses for their graduate students in her areas of expertise and giving research presentations. Additionally, she will analyze the data she gathered in the field and work on disseminating the results.&nbsp;</p>

<p>She hopes to aid her Brazilian colleagues in training native speakers, develop teaching materials for the Amazonian languages they research and assist in creating best practices on Indigenous language research.&nbsp;</p>

<p>&ldquo;Dr. Rosa Vallejos-Yop&aacute;n is an extraordinary scholar whose work helps explain the nature of linguistic structure. Her research has led to many impactful research products, from books and articles to archival collections most important for language resources for local school and teachers in the communities she work with. Her tireless and unwavering commitment is inspiring,&rdquo; said Shin.&nbsp;</p>

<p>Vallejos has been studying Amazonian languages for 27 years and &ldquo;is deeply committed&rdquo; to positively impacting the communities she works with, and with this award she hopes to foster collaborations that will outlast her time in Brazil.&nbsp;</p>

<div class=\"textImage textImage-center textImage-caption\" style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; text-align: center; width: 425px; font-size: 90%; font-style: italic;\"><img align=\"center\" alt=\"Research trips and visited communities\" author=\"\" class=\"widget-image\" custom_size=\"true\" data-imgheight=\"318\" data-imgwidth=\"425\" file_id=\"68432fd63d6332fd0448c7bd\" height=\"318\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/cms.ipressroom.com/175/files/20255/Research+trips+and+visited+communities.jpeg\" title=\"Rosa's research trips and visited communities\" width=\"425\" />
<div class=\"textImage-captionBody\" style=\"padding: 3px 0px; clear: both;\">Rosa&#39;s research trips and visited communities</div>
</div>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Learn more about Vallejos&rsquo; and her research project on her&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.unm.edu/~rvallejos/\">personal website</a>.&nbsp;</p>
