<h2>About Online Course Reviews at UNM</h2>

<p>These initiatives ensure that online courses align with the best practices outlined in the Online Learning Excellence Framework, which emphasizes essential online course design elements and strategies needed to meet the needs of UNM students.</p>

<p>UNM&#39;s commitment to supporting quality online education is evident through these initiatives. Both CTL and UNM Online offer numerous opportunities throughout the year for instructors to enhance their course design. By participating in these reviews, instructors demonstrate their dedication to continuous improvement and student success. The Foundational Course Design Review can be treated as a first step toward meeting the standards of a Golden Paw Award.</p>

<p>Instructors who complete a Foundational Course Design Review are eligible to receive $500 per course, and those awarded a Golden Paw will receive a stipend of $2,000.</p>

<p>Instructors interested in a Foundational Course Design Review can submit their interest form to participate in the Fall cycle, with the best consideration date being Aug.&nbsp;1, 2025. Calls for nominations for the next Golden Paw Award review cycle will be announced in the Fall semester.</p>

<p>For more information about the Foundational Course Design Review, visit UNM Online&rsquo;s <a href=\"https://online.unm.edu/admin-resources/foundational_course_design_review.html\">website</a>. To learn more about the Golden Paw Awards, visit the CTL&rsquo;s <a href=\"https://ctl.unm.edu/instructors/teaching-excellence/golden-paw/index.html\">website</a>.</p>
